The paper deals with a fault-tolerant distributed storage system, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The system also involves the use of erasure codes, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the system in an asynchronous message-passing environment, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
